cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the detection of disease in medical images using deep learning techniques. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also evident in the paper. The analysis of 3D volumes as a sequence of 2D images suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques for disease detection suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
